Package game

Class Game

java.lang.Object
game.Game
public class Game
extends java.lang.Object
Main Game class which initialises levels and stores key aspects towards loading new levels and levels from game files

  • Constructor Summary

    Creates the initial Game at the start level, adds the view and all mouse and key listeners as well as step listeners

  • Method Details

    • nextLevel

      public void nextLevel()
      Increments level and stores the current life and ammo counter of the playable character. Calls the new level to be generated in refreshLevel()

    • refreshLevel

      public void refreshLevel()
      Generates the level based on what level is currently assigned in the game. Adds all listeners back into the game and creates a new playable character in this world and assigns it the life and ammo count stored in Game. Used to restart a specific level or generate the next level of the game
